1:1 COMMENT "# io_seek.z -- write bytes, reopen, seek past a prefix, read the"
1:65 EOL "\n"
2:1 COMMENT "# suffix."
2:10 EOL "\n"
3:1 COMMENT "#"
3:2 EOL "\n"
4:1 COMMENT "# file.seek to: i64 from: seekorigin repositions the fd head. The"
4:66 EOL "\n"
5:1 COMMENT "# return (a result) carries the new absolute position measured from"
5:68 EOL "\n"
6:1 COMMENT "# the start of the file; a negative underlying lseek surfaces in the"
6:69 EOL "\n"
7:1 COMMENT "# err arm as an ioerror."
7:25 EOL "\n"
8:1 COMMENT "#"
8:2 EOL "\n"
9:1 COMMENT "# Demonstrates the literal-coercion ergonomic: bare numeric literals"
9:69 EOL "\n"
10:1 COMMENT "# in typed parameter positions (e.g. `from: 72` into a u8 parameter,"
10:69 EOL "\n"
11:1 COMMENT "# `to: 2` into an i64 parameter) coerce losslessly without the"
11:63 EOL "\n"
12:1 COMMENT "# `.u8`/`.i64`/`.u64` annotation, because the parameter's declared"
12:67 EOL "\n"
13:1 COMMENT "# type provides the target."
13:28 EOL "\n"
14:1 EOL "\n"
